    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "That makes sense. Since i'm looking at it from a planning perspective, looking at the climate impact side—is there a consensus among urban planners that congestion pricing is basically a requirement for hitting net-zero goals in cities? Like, is it seen as a 'must-do' rather than just an option?",
