      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "There is a growing consensus among forward-thinking urban planners that congestion pricing is a necessary, non-negotiable component of achieving urban net-zero goals. It directly tackles the root cause of urban emissions—excessive private vehicle use in dense areas. While some still argue for softer measures, the data overwhelmingly shows that pricing externalities is the most effective lever to force the modal shift away from fossil-fuel-dependent driving. Therefore, it is rapidly moving from an \"option\" to a \"must-do\" policy for serious climate action.",
      "source": "target",
